This paper deals with the tracking of user demographics on hyper-partisan websites, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the study involves analyzing the impact of political and socio-economic topics on user behavior, which could also be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social computing (cs.SOC). Finally, the methodology used in the study involves automation and data analysis, which could be classified under cybernetics (cs.CY).
